===Custom Signets===

Users can create their own signet by specifying a different challenge script:

<pre>
intcoind -signet -signetchallenge=<hex>
</pre>

Each unique challenge script produces a different network, preventing cross-contamination.

==Differences from BIP 325==

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Aspect !! BIP 325 (Bitcoin) !! IIP-56 (INTcoin)
|-
| Signature scheme || ECDSA / Schnorr || ML-DSA-87 (Dilithium5)
|-
| Challenge opcode || OP_CHECKSIG / OP_CHECKMULTISIG || OP_CHECKSIG_DILITHIUM
|-
| Default challenge || 1-of-2 multisig || Single authority key
|-
| Hash function || SHA-256d || SHA3-256
|-
| Key derivation || Manual keygen || Deterministic from seed string
|-
| Block time || 10 minutes || 2 minutes
|}

==Security Considerations==

* The signet authority key controls block production but not transaction validity
* Users can verify all transactions independently
* The challenge script is public; security relies on the private key
* Custom signets allow anyone to run their own controlled test network

